Body:
What We've Learned Updated: Issues like this often occur when a customer has conducted an SPAC scan that gathered activity involving SP resources that havenâ€™t yet been scanned with SPAA or SPSEEK. If they are reviewing this activity in the AIC immediately after importing the SPAC scan data, it could explain why the ResourceIds are null. Running an SPAA or SPSEEK scan with those resources included and then importing the results should resolve the issue.

Let me know if you continue to se the NULLs after running SPAA/SPSEEK.

"I opened this case after multiple SPAA/SPEEK runs, this is still a problem."
Next Steps Updated: R&D Backlog and investigation

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Upgrade NEA to 11.6.0.112
Remove all tables and SQLlite dbs related to sharepoint
Scan and import SP permissions and activity
Note resourceid of activity records is null
Next Steps Updated: R&D Backlog and investigation - code freeze

Next Steps Updated: Dev team has pulled this onto the sprint and is investigating
PPR to the end of sprint 4/15

Next Steps Updated: Verify the following with customer:
* Are the following event IDs present in SA_SPAC_ActivityEventsView: 3992693, 8400059, 12642013
* Is the SPAA/SPSEEK scan scoped to include the paths of SPAC?
